1
00:00:01,500 --> 00:00:04,759
Alhamdulillah. Ashhadu an la ilaha illa Allah, Wahdahu la sharika lah, wa usalli wa sallim

2
00:00:06,080 --> 00:00:15,039
Last week, and the week before, we went over time, and some of the brothers and sisters were having to catch classes at 1 o'clock, we were a little late, they had to leave.

3
00:00:15,880 --> 00:00:25,559
So I plan to finish by a quarter to 1, inshallah. However, I'm already 5 minutes late. I cheated myself out of 5 minutes.

4
00:00:25,559 --> 00:00:29,839
So, I will try to compress everything in the next half hour.

5
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:39,039
The problem with most people is unawareness of God, or underestimating the greatness of God.

6
00:00:39,240 --> 00:00:43,520
So, the subject today is awareness.

7
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:49,439
You look at the people in the streets, see how they are going about their lives, unaware of their Creator.

8
00:00:50,039 --> 00:00:55,439
So we're going to look at a few verses in here to see the importance of being aware.

9
00:00:55,780 --> 00:01:07,480
The first one is in Surah 7, verse 179, page 117, it says,

10
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:11,000
"We have committed to Hell multitudes of jinn and humans.

11
00:01:11,519 --> 00:01:15,859
They are the ones who have hearts, have minds, but they're minds

12
00:01:15,859 --> 00:01:22,280
that do not understand, eyes that do not see, and ears that do not hear. They are

13
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:25,560
like animals; no, they're even worse. They are the unaware."

14
00:01:27,579 --> 00:01:33,859
So the people who are unaware are assigned to Hell. They have minds with

15
00:01:33,859 --> 00:01:37,799
which they do not think, they have eyes with which they do not see, and they have

16
00:01:37,799 --> 00:01:42,840
ears with which they do not hear. The next verse is in Surah 10, verse 7.

17
00:01:52,439 --> 00:01:59,340
It says, "Indeed, those who do not expect to meet us, are satisfied and content with

18
00:01:59,340 --> 00:02:03,019
this life, and are heedless of our revelations.

19
00:02:04,719 --> 00:02:07,780
These have deserved Hell as a consequence of their work."

20
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:14,080
Now, "heedless" or "unaware," it is the same Arabic word, which means they are unaware.

21
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:18,599
And you notice they are content with this life.

22
00:02:18,979 --> 00:02:21,699
So you look at the majority of people out there on the street,

23
00:02:21,879 --> 00:02:25,719
and they are unaware of their Creator, unaware of the Hereafter,

24
00:02:27,460 --> 00:02:29,919
accountability, and they are busy with this life.

25
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:36,340
The next verse, 16, 106.

26
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:47,259
It says,

27
00:02:47,319 --> 00:02:54,199
"Anyone who disbelieves in God after having believed—except for one who is forced while the heart is content with faith—

28
00:02:55,060 --> 00:02:57,319
but whoever willingly opens his heart to disbelief, has incurred wrath from God..."
